<% module_prefix = name.split('.').first %>
You have just created a new dojo module called: <%= name %>.common

To use your new <%= name %>.common module in your application, just edit your layout or view
so that it includes the following code:

<script type="text/javascript" src="/javascripts/dojo/dojo/dojo.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">
  dojo.registerModulePath("<%= module_prefix %>", "/javascripts/<%= module_prefix %>");
  dojo.require("<%= name %>.common");
</script>